# Skip optional dependencies on install.
#
# wrangler ships platform-specific workerd binaries (one per OS/arch)
# as optional deps. When the lockfile is generated on macOS, npm pins
# the darwin variant; that breaks `npm ci` on Cloudflare's Linux build
# runner, which strictly enforces the lockfile.
#
# The workerd binary is only needed for local `wrangler dev` — the
# build (`astro build`) and deploy (`wrangler deploy`) paths don't
# need it. Safe to skip in CI.
omit=optional
